21 "§ 90-756. Requirements for licensure.
22 (a) A person seeking to obtain a license for a radiologic imaging or radiation therapy
23 modality shall comply with each of the following requirements:
24 (1) At least 18 years of age at the time of application.
25 (2) Has a high school diploma or has passed an approved equivalency test.
26 (b) Limited Practice Radiographer. – In addition to the requirements of subsection (a) of
27 this section, a person seeking to obtain a license as a limited radiologist assistant shall comply
28 with each of the following requirements:
29 (1) Successfully complete a course of study in limited X-ray machine operation
30 approved by the Board.
31 (2) Pass an examination in limited X-ray machine operation approved by the
32 Board from the following examinations:
33 a. The American Registry of Radiologic Technologists limited X-ray
34 machine operator examination for limited bone density, chest,
35 extremities, spine, skull/sinus, and podiatric radiography.
36 b. The International Society for Clinical Densitometry examination in
37 clinical bone densitometry.
38 c. A certification organization recognized by the Board.
39 (c) Magnetic Resonance Technologist License. – In addition to the requirements of
40 subsection (a) of this section, a person seeking to obtain a license as a magnetic resonance
41 technologist shall comply with each of the following requirements:
42 (1) Successfully complete a course of study in magnetic resonance imaging or a
43 course in radiography and additional educational requirements in magnetic
44 resonance technology approved by the Board.
45 (2) Possess current certification and registration in radiography from the
46 American Registry of Radiologic Technologists or current certification and
47 registration in magnetic resonance from the American Registry of Radiologic
48 Technologists or a certification organization approved by the Board.
49 (3) By January 1, 2026, all applicants for a license under this subsection shall be
50 certified in magnetic resonance under subdivision (2) of this subsection.
