1 "§ 90-757. Examinations.
2 (a) Evidence of Examination. – To meet the requirement of examination under this
3 Article for nuclear medicine technology, radiation therapy, radiography, radiologist assistant, or
4 sonography, the Board shall accept current certification and registration by a certification
5 organization recognized by the Board in the applicant's or licensee's modality.
6 (b) Limited Practice Radiographer Examination. – The Board shall use a limited practice
7 radiographer examination administered by the American Registry of Radiologic Technologists
8 for persons applying for a limited practice radiographer license and permit in chest, extremity,
9 spine, skull/sinus, or podiatric radiography or bone densitometry testing. The Board shall
10 determine by regulation the examination score that constitutes successful completion.
11 (c) Acceptance of Chiropractic Radiologic Technologist Certification. – The Board may
12 accept certification and registration from a certification organization approved by the Board to
13 meet the requirement of this subsection for successful completion of an examination for a person
14 applying for a limited practice radiographer license and permit in spine radiography who works
15 under the supervision of a chiropractor.
16 "§ 90-758. Issuance of license; temporary license; display of license.
17 (a) Issuance of License. – The Board shall issue a license to an applicant who meets the
18 requirements for licensure specified in this Article and the regulations adopted by the Board,
19 verified by oath or affirmation, upon payment of a fee as provided in G.S. 90-761.
20 (b) The Board may issue a license with authorization to perform more than one medical
21 imaging or radiation therapy modality if the person is qualified in each modality.
22 (c) Temporary License. – The Board may issue a temporary license to any person whose
23 license or license renewal may be pending or when issuance is for providing medical imaging or
24 radiation therapy services to medically underserved areas as determined by the Board.
25 (d) New graduates awaiting national certification may be issued a provisional license for
26 employment purposes for a period not to exceed one year.
27 (e) Temporary License for Cross-Training. – A person licensed under this Article may
28 apply to the Board for a temporary license in an additional medical imaging or radiation therapy
29 modality to complete clinical experience requirements for an applicable training pathway
30 established by a certification organization recognized by the Board. Temporary licenses issued
31 for training purposes shall expire three years after issuance.
32 (f) Display of License; License to Be Available Upon Request. – The copy of the current
33 license of all license holders must be maintained at their places of employment.
34 "§ 90-759. Educational programs approved by the Board.
35 (a) In order to obtain approval by the Board, educational programs in medical imaging
36 or radiation therapy shall (i) be offered by a medical facility or educational institution and (ii) be
37 affiliated with one or more hospitals or clinics to provide the requisite clinical education.
38 (b) The curriculum for each course of study in medical imaging or radiation therapy shall
39 be no less stringent than the standards approved by the Joint Review Committee on Education in
40 Radiologic Technology, the Joint Review Committee on Education in Nuclear Medicine
41 Technology, the Commission on Accreditation of Allied Health Education Programs, or other
42 educational accreditation agency approved by the Board.
43 "§ 90-760. License renewal; reciprocity.
44 (a) Every license issued under this Article shall expire on the last day of the licensee's
45 month of birth in the second year following the year of issuance. A licensee who fails to renew a
46 license prior to the expiration date shall submit an application for reinstatement to obtain
47 licensure. The license shall be renewed upon the payment of a renewal fee, as provided in
48 G.S. 90-761, if, at the time of application for renewal, the applicant is not in violation of this
49 Article and has complied with any continuing education requirements pursuant to rules adopted
50 by the Board.
