1 (b) The Board shall notify a licensee at least 60 days in advance of the expiration of his
2 or her license. The licensee shall inform the Board of any change of the licensee's address. Each
3 licensee is responsible for renewing his or her license before the expiration date. Licenses that
4 are not renewed automatically lapse.
5 (c) The Board may provide for the late renewal of an automatically lapsed license upon
6 the payment of a reinstatement fee. The licensee shall maintain certification in his or her licensed
7 specialty throughout the licensure period established by the credentialing body.
8 (d) The Board may, upon application and payment of proper fees, issue a license to a
9 person who has been licensed, registered, or certified to perform medical imaging or radiation
10 therapy procedures in another jurisdiction if that jurisdiction's standards are substantially
11 equivalent to those provided in this Article and the regulations adopted by the Board.
12 "§ 90-761. Fees.
13 (a) The Board is authorized to charge and collect fees not to exceed the following:
14 (1) Initial, provisional, or temporary license application fee, one hundred dollars
15 ($100.00).
16 (2) Biennial license fee, one hundred fifty dollars ($150.00).
17 (3) Temporary license fee, one hundred dollars ($100.00).
18 (4) Duplicate license, twenty-five dollars ($25.00).
19 (5) License renewal late fee, seventy-five dollars ($75.00).
20 (b) All fees shall be set by the Board pursuant to rules adopted under this Article. All fees
21 payable to the Board shall be deposited in the name of the Board in financial institutions
22 designated by the Board as official depositories and shall be used to pay all expenses incurred in
23 carrying out the purposes of this Article.
24 (c) All salaries, compensation, and expenses incurred to carry out the purposes of this
25 Article shall be paid by the Board exclusively out of the fees received by the Board as authorized
26 by this Article or out of funds received from other sources.
27 "§ 90-762. Disciplinary authority.
28 (a) The Board may deny, suspend, revoke, or refuse to renew a license or impose
29 probationary conditions on a license if the licensee or applicant for licensure has engaged in any
30 of the following conduct:
31 (1) Obtaining a license by means of fraud, misrepresentation, or concealment of
32 material facts.
33 (2) Engaging in unprofessional conduct pursuant to rules adopted by the Board.
34 (3) Having been convicted of or pleaded guilty or nolo contendere to a crime
35 involving moral turpitude or any crime that indicates that the licensee or
36 applicant is unfit or incompetent to administer medical imaging or radiation
37 therapy procedures or that the licensee or applicant has deceived or defrauded
38 the public.
39 (4) Engaging in any act or practice in violation of any of the provisions of this
40 Article or any rule adopted by the Board or aiding, abetting, or assisting any
41 person in a violation.
42 (5) Committing an act or acts of malpractice, gross negligence, or incompetence
43 in administering medical imaging or radiation therapy procedures.
44 (6) Practicing as a person licensed to administer medical imaging or radiation
45 therapy procedures without a current license.
46 (7) Engaging in conduct that could result in harm or injury to the public.
47 (8) Being unfit or incompetent to administer medical imaging or radiation therapy
48 services by reason of deliberate or negligent acts or omissions, regardless of
49 whether actual injury to a patient is established.
50 (b) The denial, refusal to renew, suspension, revocation, or imposition of probationary
51 conditions upon a license may be ordered by the Board after a hearing held in accordance with
